Money Stuff =0A A crude model for sell-side equity research might go someth=
ing like this: =0AThere are a lot of buy-side investment firms =E2=80=94 mu=
tual funds, asset =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=
=3D825881&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12262192&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525=
&p=3D01092025>=0A=0A=0A=0ANo research=0A=0AA crude model for sell-side equi=
ty research might go something like this:=0A=0A * There are a lot of buy-si=
de investment firms =E2=80=94 mutual funds, asset =0Amanagers, etc. =E2=80=
=94 each of which can invest in the same large universe of =0Athousands of =
companies. =0A * They all try to do research, understand the companies, and=
 invest in the =0Agood ones. =0A * It is hard for one person to really unde=
rstand more than one or two =0Asectors, and more than a couple of dozen com=
panies, in great depth. =0A * A typical medium-size asset manager can=E2=80=
=99t really hire hundreds of analysts =0Ato get to know every company in de=
