e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This paper describes a process for automatically gene=
rating academic finance papers using large language models (LLMs). It demon=
strates the process' efficacy by producing hundreds of complete papers on s=
tock return predictability, a topic particularly well-suited for our illust=
ration. We first mine over 30,000 potential stock return predictor signals =
from accounting data, and apply the Novy-Marx and Velikov (2024) "Assaying =
